  <main class="wrap">
    <h2>It starts with noticing a gap</h2>
    <p>Every business I've built started the same way — I noticed something was missing, not from market research, but from actually living it. I live in the Oxford/Villages area of Central Florida, and golf carts are part of daily life here the way a second car would be anywhere else. When I kept running into the same friction points as a golf cart owner myself, that became Villages Golf Cart Trader and, later, Cartzilla.</p>

    <h2>Villages Golf Cart Trader: solving a local problem</h2>
    <p>Before Villages Golf Cart Trader existed, buying or selling a cart locally meant crowded Facebook groups where listings disappear in hours, or generic classifieds sites with no local focus. I built a free, simple marketplace specifically for The Villages community — because a place this specific to golf cart culture deserved a marketplace built just as specifically for it.</p>

    <h2>Cartzilla: built from hands-on experience</h2>
    <p>Cartzilla grew out of the same instinct, applied to parts and accessories. I've spent plenty of time working on my own cart — electrical systems, battery issues, the usual maintenance every owner eventually deals with — and that hands-on experience shapes which products end up in the store. It's a business built by an owner, not a distributor guessing at what golf cart owners need.</p>

    <h2>Florida Buzz: a different kind of outlet</h2>
    <p>Florida Buzz is a different project — a Florida travel and lifestyle publication rather than a marketplace — but it comes from the same place: an interest in Florida as a place worth writing about and building for, beyond just my day-to-day sales career.</p>

    <h2>What ties it all together</h2>
    <p>None of these businesses came from chasing a trend. Each started because I saw something real and specific that was missing, and I was in a position to just go build it. That's the same instinct that's carried through my career in healthcare and animal health sales — find the actual problem, then solve it properly, and let the relationships and reputation follow from doing that well.</p>
    <p>You can read more about my <a href="/career-journey">career journey</a> in healthcare and animal health sales, see my full <a href="/resume">resume</a>, or head back to my <a href="/">main profile</a>.</p>
